  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity Enhancement for Institutionalized Victim-Centred Investigations and Prosecutions of Trafficking in Persons Cases in South Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will contribute to the Government of South Africa and civil society efforts to uphold the rights of victims of trafficking (TIP) and increase prosecution of trafficking in persons cases. The project will contribute towards sensitizing and strengthening the already established anti-TIP task forces to actively identify, assist and prosecute TIP cases.  Additionally, the project will focus on mainstreaming a counter trafficking curriculum into the training programs of targeted government departments to ensure that relevant officers at all levels have an understanding of TIP and victim centered assistance. Targeted departments for this project are the South African Police Services, Department of Labor, National Prosecuting Authority, Department of Social Development, Department of Home Affairs, Department of Justice and Department of Health. Members of the civil society organizations will also be reached through the TIP task forces.</narrative>
  </description>
